{{unsourced|date=January 2018}}
A '''game call''' is a device that is used to mimic animal noises to attract or drive animals to a [[hunter]]. Animal species attracted to game calls include deer, turkey, ducks, geese, moose, elk, raccoons, wild pigs, coyotes, and crows.
