[[File:Haus Graf Anton Günther building, Oldenburg.JPG|thumb|The Haus Graf Anton Günther historic building in Oldenburg.]] [[File:Haus Graf Anton Günther mural, Oldenburg.JPG|thumb|Mural on the outside of the Haus Graf Anton Günther building depicting [[Anthony Günther, Count of Oldenburg]].]]
The '''Haus "Graf Anton Günther"''' (aka '''Hotel Graf Anton Günther''') is a historic house in central [[Oldenburg]], [[Germany]], dating from 1682.<ref>{{cite| url=http://www.oldenburg-tourist.de/ | title=Oldenburg | publisher=Oldenburg Tourist }}</ref>
[[Anthony Günther, Count of Oldenburg|Count Anton Günther]] is depicted riding a horse on the facade, which was redesigned in the [[neo-Renaissance]] style in 1894. The house was used by merchants and [[tobacco]] manufacturers.
After the great fire in Oldenburg, the building was constructed in 1682 as a merchant's house on the Lange Straße.<ref name="alt-oldenburg">{{cite web| url=http://alt-oldenburg.de/straen-l-z/lange-strae/hotel-graf-anton-guenther/index.html | title=Restaurant und Hotel Graf Anton Günther | website=[http://alt-oldenburg.de/ Alt-Oldenburg] | language=German | location=Germany | accessdate=26 September 2015 }}</ref> For 135 years it belonged to the [[Grovermann]] family. In 1828, it was bought by [[Hinrich Lebrecht Kirchhoff]]. In 1838, the tobacco manufacturer [[Johann Karl Propping]] acquired the property. Propping built a tobacco factory designed by the architect [[Klingenberg (architect)|Klingenberg]]. The house changed hands several times in the 1890s until it was bought by the [[Hoyer brewery]]. The house became a restaurant and hotel in 1894 and was named "Graf Anton Günther".<ref name="holiday-check">{{cite web| url=http://www.holidaycheck.de/reisetipp-Urlaubsbilder+Altstadt+Oldenburg-ch_ub-zid_40708.html?action=detail&mediaId=1157437975 | title=Bürgerhaus/Hotel Graf-Anton-Günther-Haus – Altstadt Oldenburg | website=[http://www.holidaycheck.de/ HolidayCheck] | language=German | location=Germany | accessdate=26 September 2015 }}</ref> Professor [[August Oetken]] created the large exterior fresco of Count Anton Günther on his horse, Kranich.<ref name="alt-oldenburg" />
