{{Paraguay-mil-bio-stub}}

The '''United States Army Medical Research Unit-Kenya''' ('''USAMRU-K''') — sometimes known informally as the "Walter Reed Project" — is a "Special Foreign Activity" of the [[Walter Reed Army Institute of Research]] headquartered in [[Nairobi, Kenya]].<ref>[http://www.usamrukenya.org/ USAMRU-Kenya]</ref> The unit was established in 1969 and operates under a cooperative agreement with the [[Kenya Medical Research Institute]]. Much of the research done there has focused on tropical diseases, such as [[malaria]], [[trypanosomiasis]], and [[leishmaniasis]], as well as arboviruses, [[HIV/AIDS]], and other emerging infectious diseases.
==See also== *[[United States Army Medical Research Unit-Brazil]] (USAMRU-B) *[[United States Army Medical Research Unit-Europe]] (USAMRU-E) *[[Makerere University Walter Reed Project]] (MUWRP)
